epochs.name: Prescreening
epochs.description: Assessment of eGFR and UACR based on local laboratory results within 6 months prior to screening.

epochs.name: Screening
epochs.description: Up to 8 weeks period to assess eligibility and stabilize background ACEi/ARB therapy.

epochs.name: Single-Blind Placebo Run-In
epochs.description: 2-week period (Week -2 to Day 1) where subjects take single-blind placebo to assess compliance.

epochs.name: Double-Blind Treatment Phase
epochs.description: Randomized treatment period starting at Day 1 until the Global Trial End Date (GTED), estimated 5 to 5.5 years.

epochs.name: Post-Treatment Follow-up
epochs.description: Telephone contact or visit approximately 30 days after the last dose of study drug.
